    "excerpt": "This piyyut versifies the Laws of Prayer as derived from the verses recounting Hannah’s prayer (TB Berakhot 31a-31b). In addition to using the words of the verses from which these laws are derived, this poem is itself a prayer: «Train my lips to pray like those of Hannah!». It can be sung as a <em>reshut</em> (introductory piyyut) for the Haftarah of the first day of Rosh Hashanah, when these verses are read.  . . .",
    "content": "<div class=\"english\" lang=\"eng-Latn\" style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">\nThis piyyut versifies the Laws of Prayer as derived from the verses recounting Hannah’s prayer (Bavli Berakhot 31a-31b). In addition to using the words of the verses from which these laws are derived, this poem is itself a prayer: «Train my lips to pray like those of Hannah!». It can be sung as a <em>reshut</em> (introductory piyyut) for the Haftarah of the first day of Rosh Hashanah, when these verses are read. You can read the commentary of the piyyut in Hebrew <a href=\"https://www.nli.org.il/he/piyut/Piyut1song_013180000000005171/NLI\">here</a>.\n</div>\n<hr />\n<table style=\"margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\" class=\"draggable toggleable-table\">\n<thead>\n<tr>\n<th id=\"x\" style=\"text-align: right;\">Source (Hebrew)</th>\n<th style=\"text-align: left;\">Translation (French)</th>\n<th style=\"text-align: left;\">Translation (English)</th>\n</tr>\n</thead>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"vertical-align:top;\">\n<div class=\"liturgy\" lang=\"heb-Hebr\" style=\"text-align: right;\">\nאֵל אֲשֶׁר חַסְדּוֹ לֹא מָנַע<br />\nתּוֹךְ עַמּוֹ מִשְׁכָּנוֹ חָנָה<br />\nנִקְדַּשׁ בְּפִי עֲדַת עַם נָע<br />\nלַמֵּד פִּי פַלֵּל כְּחַנָּה\n</div>\n</td>\n<td style=\"vertical-align:top;\">\n<div class=\"french\" lang=\"fra-Latn\" style=\"text-align: left;\">\nÔ Éternel qui sa bonté ne retint,<br />\nQui, au sein de son peuple, daigna résider<br />\nPour être sanctifié par le verbe de ses assemblées,<br />\nForme mes lèvres à la prière comme Hanna.\n</div>\n</td>\n<td style=\"vertical-align:top;\">\n<div class=\"english\" lang=\"eng-Latn\" style=\"text-align: left;\">\nO Lord, who does not withhold His kindness,<span class=\"footnote_referrer\"><a role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\" onclick=\"footnote_moveToReference__1('footnote_plugin_reference__1_1');\" onkeypress=\"footnote_moveToReference__1('footnote_plugin_reference__1_1');\" ><sup id=\"footnote_plugin_tooltip__1_1\" class=\"footnote_plugin_tooltip_text\">[1]</sup></a><span id=\"footnote_plugin_tooltip_text__1_1\" class=\"footnote_tooltip\"> Find Genesis 27:27&nbsp;</span></span><script type=\"text/javascript\"> jQuery('#footnote_plugin_tooltip__1_1').tooltip({ tip: '#footnote_plugin_tooltip_text__1_1', tipClass: 'footnote_tooltip', effect: 'fade', predelay: 0, fadeInSpeed: 200, delay: 400, fadeOutSpeed: 200, position: 'center right', relative: true, offset: [0, 0], });</script><br />\nWho among His people does reside<span class=\"footnote_referrer\"><a role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\" onclick=\"footnote_moveToReference__1('footnote_plugin_reference__1_2');\" onkeypress=\"footnote_moveToReference__1('footnote_plugin_reference__1_2');\" ><sup id=\"footnote_plugin_tooltip__1_2\" class=\"footnote_plugin_tooltip_text\">[2]</sup></a><span id=\"footnote_plugin_tooltip_text__1_2\" class=\"footnote_tooltip\"> Find Exodus 25:8, Exodus 29:45&nbsp;</span></span><script type=\"text/javascript\"> jQuery('#footnote_plugin_tooltip__1_2').tooltip({ tip: '#footnote_plugin_tooltip_text__1_2', tipClass: 'footnote_tooltip', effect: 'fade', predelay: 0, fadeInSpeed: 200, delay: 400, fadeOutSpeed: 200, position: 'center right', relative: true, offset: [0, 0], });</script><br />\nTo be sanctified by the mouths<span class=\"footnote_referrer\"><a role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\" onclick=\"footnote_moveToReference__1('footnote_plugin_reference__1_3');\" onkeypress=\"footnote_moveToReference__1('footnote_plugin_reference__1_3');\" ><sup id=\"footnote_plugin_tooltip__1_3\" class=\"footnote_plugin_tooltip_text\">[3]</sup></a><span id=\"footnote_plugin_tooltip_text__1_3\" class=\"footnote_tooltip\"> The presence of an <em>edah</em> (congregation) is required for the recitation of “sacred words.” Find Berachot 21b, Megillah 23b&nbsp;</span></span><script type=\"text/javascript\"> jQuery('#footnote_plugin_tooltip__1_3').tooltip({ tip: '#footnote_plugin_tooltip_text__1_3', tipClass: 'footnote_tooltip', effect: 'fade', predelay: 0, fadeInSpeed: 200, delay: 400, fadeOutSpeed: 200, position: 'center right', relative: true, offset: [0, 0], });</script> of His multitudes:<span class=\"footnote_referrer\"><a role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\" onclick=\"footnote_moveToReference__1('footnote_plugin_reference__1_4');\" onkeypress=\"footnote_moveToReference__1('footnote_plugin_reference__1_4');\" ><sup id=\"footnote_plugin_tooltip__1_4\" class=\"footnote_plugin_tooltip_text\">[4]</sup></a><span id=\"footnote_plugin_tooltip_text__1_4\" class=\"footnote_tooltip\"> Per Jeremiah 14:10, a people accustomed to traveling.&nbsp;</span></span><script type=\"text/javascript\"> jQuery('#footnote_plugin_tooltip__1_4').tooltip({ tip: '#footnote_plugin_tooltip_text__1_4', tipClass: 'footnote_tooltip', effect: 'fade', predelay: 0, fadeInSpeed: 200, delay: 400, fadeOutSpeed: 200, position: 'center right', relative: true, offset: [0, 0], });</script><br />\nTrain my lips to pray like those of Ḥannah!<span class=\"footnote_referrer\"><a role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\" onclick=\"footnote_moveToReference__1('footnote_plugin_reference__1_5');\" onkeypress=\"footnote_moveToReference__1('footnote_plugin_reference__1_5');\" ><sup id=\"footnote_plugin_tooltip__1_5\" class=\"footnote_plugin_tooltip_text\">[5]</sup></a><span id=\"footnote_plugin_tooltip_text__1_5\" class=\"footnote_tooltip\"> An allusion to the statement of Rav Hamnuna in Berakhot 31a: “How many great halakhot can be learned from the verses of Ḥannah&#8217;s prayer!”&nbsp;</span></span><script type=\"text/javascript\"> jQuery('#footnote_plugin_tooltip__1_5').tooltip({ tip: '#footnote_plugin_tooltip_text__1_5', tipClass: 'footnote_tooltip', effect: 'fade', predelay: 0, fadeInSpeed: 200, delay: 400, fadeOutSpeed: 200, position: 'center right', relative: true, offset: [0, 0], });</script>\n</div>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"vertical-align:top;\">\n<div class=\"liturgy\" lang=\"heb-Hebr\" style=\"text-align: right;\">\n<span class=\"instruction\">{שכרות}</span><br />\nרַחוּם נַחֵם נֶֽפֶשׁ מָרָה<br />\nבְּלֶב־טוֹב לְעָבְדְּךָ נָּא<br />\nכִּי לֹא מִיַּֽיִן שְׁכוּרָה<br />\nנַפְשִׁי בוֹכִיָּה כְּחַנָּה\n</div>\n</td>\n<td style=\"vertical-align:top;\">\n<div class=\"french\" lang=\"fra-Latn\" style=\"text-align: left;\">\n&nbsp;<br />\nÔ Miséricordieux, console mon âme amère,<br />\nQu’il lui soit permis de Te servir dans l’allégresse,<br />\nCar ce n’est point le vin qui étourdit<br />\nMon âme attristée comme celle de Hanna.\n</div>\n</td>\n<td style=\"vertical-align:top;\">\n<div class=\"english\" lang=\"eng-Latn\" style=\"text-align: left;\">\n&nbsp;<br />\nO Merciful One, console my bitter soul,<span class=\"footnote_referrer\"><a role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\" onclick=\"footnote_moveToReference__1('footnote_plugin_reference__1_6');\" onkeypress=\"footnote_moveToReference__1('footnote_plugin_reference__1_6');\" ><sup id=\"footnote_plugin_tooltip__1_6\" class=\"footnote_plugin_tooltip_text\">[6]</sup></a><span id=\"footnote_plugin_tooltip_text__1_6\" class=\"footnote_tooltip\"> According to Ḥannah&#8217;s self-description in I Samuel 1:10&nbsp;</span></span><script type=\"text/javascript\"> jQuery('#footnote_plugin_tooltip__1_6').tooltip({ tip: '#footnote_plugin_tooltip_text__1_6', tipClass: 'footnote_tooltip', effect: 'fade', predelay: 0, fadeInSpeed: 200, delay: 400, fadeOutSpeed: 200, position: 'center right', relative: true, offset: [0, 0], });</script><br />\nAllow it only to serve You<span class=\"footnote_referrer\"><a role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\" onclick=\"footnote_moveToReference__1('footnote_plugin_reference__1_7');\" onkeypress=\"footnote_moveToReference__1('footnote_plugin_reference__1_7');\" ><sup id=\"footnote_plugin_tooltip__1_7\" class=\"footnote_plugin_tooltip_text\">[7]</sup></a><span id=\"footnote_plugin_tooltip_text__1_7\" class=\"footnote_tooltip\"> Prayer is called “work that is in the heart” in Tractate Ta&#8217;anit 2:1&nbsp;</span></span><script type=\"text/javascript\"> jQuery('#footnote_plugin_tooltip__1_7').tooltip({ tip: '#footnote_plugin_tooltip_text__1_7', tipClass: 'footnote_tooltip', effect: 'fade', predelay: 0, fadeInSpeed: 200, delay: 400, fadeOutSpeed: 200, position: 'center right', relative: true, offset: [0, 0], });</script> with joy,<span class=\"footnote_referrer\"><a role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\" onclick=\"footnote_moveToReference__1('footnote_plugin_reference__1_8');\" onkeypress=\"footnote_moveToReference__1('footnote_plugin_reference__1_8');\" ><sup id=\"footnote_plugin_tooltip__1_8\" class=\"footnote_plugin_tooltip_text\">[8]</sup></a><span id=\"footnote_plugin_tooltip_text__1_8\" class=\"footnote_tooltip\"> So that she may succeed in praying to You with joy, as stated in the Baraita: One does not stand to pray [&#8230;] except with the joy of a mitsvah (Berakhot 31a).&nbsp;</span></span><script type=\"text/javascript\"> jQuery('#footnote_plugin_tooltip__1_8').tooltip({ tip: '#footnote_plugin_tooltip_text__1_8', tipClass: 'footnote_tooltip', effect: 'fade', predelay: 0, fadeInSpeed: 200, delay: 400, fadeOutSpeed: 200, position: 'center right', relative: true, offset: [0, 0], });</script><br />\nFor it is not wine that stupefies<span class=\"footnote_referrer\"><a role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\" onclick=\"footnote_moveToReference__1('footnote_plugin_reference__1_9');\" onkeypress=\"footnote_moveToReference__1('footnote_plugin_reference__1_9');\" ><sup id=\"footnote_plugin_tooltip__1_9\" class=\"footnote_plugin_tooltip_text\">[9]</sup></a><span id=\"footnote_plugin_tooltip_text__1_9\" class=\"footnote_tooltip\"> An allusion to the halakhah that a drunk person is forbidden to pray, which is learned (in Berakhot there) from Eli&#8217;s description of Ḥannah&#8217;s prayer in I Samuel. This expression is taken from the verse “and drunk, but not with wine” (Isaiah 51:21) and means to lose one&#8217;s mind as a result of distress.&nbsp;</span></span><script type=\"text/javascript\"> jQuery('#footnote_plugin_tooltip__1_9').tooltip({ tip: '#footnote_plugin_tooltip_text__1_9', tipClass: 'footnote_tooltip', effect: 'fade', predelay: 0, fadeInSpeed: 200, delay: 400, fadeOutSpeed: 200, position: 'center right', relative: true, offset: [0, 0], });</script><br />\nMy soul, grieving like that of Ḥannah.<span class=\"footnote_referrer\"><a role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\" onclick=\"footnote_moveToReference__1('footnote_plugin_reference__1_10');\" onkeypress=\"footnote_moveToReference__1('footnote_plugin_reference__1_10');\" ><sup id=\"footnote_plugin_tooltip__1_10\" class=\"footnote_plugin_tooltip_text\">[10]</sup></a><span id=\"footnote_plugin_tooltip_text__1_10\" class=\"footnote_tooltip\"> Ibid I Samuel 1:10&nbsp;</span></span><script type=\"text/javascript\"> jQuery('#footnote_plugin_tooltip__1_10').tooltip({ tip: '#footnote_plugin_tooltip_text__1_10', tipClass: 'footnote_tooltip', effect: 'fade', predelay: 0, fadeInSpeed: 200, delay: 400, fadeOutSpeed: 200, position: 'center right', relative: true, offset: [0, 0], });</script>\n</div>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"vertical-align:top;\">\n<div class=\"liturgy\" lang=\"heb-Hebr\" style=\"text-align: right;\">\n<span class=\"instruction\">{ארבע אמות}</span><br />\nבְּגַפִּי כִּי אֶתְיַצְּבָה<br />\nאֲבַקֵּשׁ נָּא הַצְלִיחָה נָּא<br />\nצָֽמְאָה נַפְשִׁי תָּאֲבָה<br />\nחַלּוֹת פָּנֶֽיךָ כְּחַנָּה\n</div>\n</td>\n<td style=\"vertical-align:top;\">\n<div class=\"french\" lang=\"fra-Latn\" style=\"text-align: left;\">\n&nbsp;<br />\nSolitaire, je me tiens debout<br />\nEt demande «donne-moi le succès»;<br />\nMon âme est fiévreuse d’<br />\nImplorer Ta face qu’interpella Hanna.\n</div>\n</td>\n<td style=\"vertical-align:top;\">\n<div class=\"english\" lang=\"eng-Latn\" style=\"text-align: left;\">\n&nbsp;<br />\nAlone<span class=\"footnote_referrer\"><a role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\" onclick=\"footnote_moveToReference__1('footnote_plugin_reference__1_11');\" onkeypress=\"footnote_moveToReference__1('footnote_plugin_reference__1_11');\" ><sup id=\"footnote_plugin_tooltip__1_11\" class=\"footnote_plugin_tooltip_text\">[11]</sup></a><span id=\"footnote_plugin_tooltip_text__1_11\" class=\"footnote_tooltip\"> Alone by myself, an allusion to the words of the Gemara that it is forbidden to sit within four cubits of a person who is praying (Berakhot 31b).&nbsp;</span></span><script type=\"text/javascript\"> jQuery('#footnote_plugin_tooltip__1_11').tooltip({ tip: '#footnote_plugin_tooltip_text__1_11', tipClass: 'footnote_tooltip', effect: 'fade', predelay: 0, fadeInSpeed: 200, delay: 400, fadeOutSpeed: 200, position: 'center right', relative: true, offset: [0, 0], });</script> I stand<span class=\"footnote_referrer\"><a role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\" onclick=\"footnote_moveToReference__1('footnote_plugin_reference__1_12');\" onkeypress=\"footnote_moveToReference__1('footnote_plugin_reference__1_12');\" ><sup id=\"footnote_plugin_tooltip__1_12\" class=\"footnote_plugin_tooltip_text\">[12]</sup></a><span id=\"footnote_plugin_tooltip_text__1_12\" class=\"footnote_tooltip\"> to pray, as Ḥannah said in relation to her prayer: “I am the woman who stands here before you praying” (I Samuel 1:26).&nbsp;</span></span><script type=\"text/javascript\"> jQuery('#footnote_plugin_tooltip__1_12').tooltip({ tip: '#footnote_plugin_tooltip_text__1_12', tipClass: 'footnote_tooltip', effect: 'fade', predelay: 0, fadeInSpeed: 200, delay: 400, fadeOutSpeed: 200, position: 'center right', relative: true, offset: [0, 0], });</script><br />\nAnd ask &#8220;May I succeed!&#8221;<span class=\"footnote_referrer\"><a role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\" onclick=\"footnote_moveToReference__1('footnote_plugin_reference__1_13');\" onkeypress=\"footnote_moveToReference__1('footnote_plugin_reference__1_13');\" ><sup id=\"footnote_plugin_tooltip__1_13\" class=\"footnote_plugin_tooltip_text\">[13]</sup></a><span id=\"footnote_plugin_tooltip_text__1_13\" class=\"footnote_tooltip\"> According to Psalms 118:25&nbsp;</span></span><script type=\"text/javascript\"> jQuery('#footnote_plugin_tooltip__1_13').tooltip({ tip: '#footnote_plugin_tooltip_text__1_13', tipClass: 'footnote_tooltip', effect: 'fade', predelay: 0, fadeInSpeed: 200, delay: 400, fadeOutSpeed: 200, position: 'center right', relative: true, offset: [0, 0], });</script>;<br />\nMy soul thirsts with desire<span class=\"footnote_referrer\"><a role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\" onclick=\"footnote_moveToReference__1('footnote_plugin_reference__1_14');\" onkeypress=\"footnote_moveToReference__1('footnote_plugin_reference__1_14');\" ><sup id=\"footnote_plugin_tooltip__1_14\" class=\"footnote_plugin_tooltip_text\">[14]</sup></a><span id=\"footnote_plugin_tooltip_text__1_14\" class=\"footnote_tooltip\"> According to Psalms 42:3&nbsp;</span></span><script type=\"text/javascript\"> jQuery('#footnote_plugin_tooltip__1_14').tooltip({ tip: '#footnote_plugin_tooltip_text__1_14', tipClass: 'footnote_tooltip', effect: 'fade', predelay: 0, fadeInSpeed: 200, delay: 400, fadeOutSpeed: 200, position: 'center right', relative: true, offset: [0, 0], });</script><br />\nTo encounter You,<span class=\"footnote_referrer\"><a role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\" onclick=\"footnote_moveToReference__1('footnote_plugin_reference__1_15');\" onkeypress=\"footnote_moveToReference__1('footnote_plugin_reference__1_15');\" ><sup id=\"footnote_plugin_tooltip__1_15\" class=\"footnote_plugin_tooltip_text\">[15]</sup></a><span id=\"footnote_plugin_tooltip_text__1_15\" class=\"footnote_tooltip\"> In the style of <em>baqashah</em> and <em>tefilah</em> (in plea and prayer)&nbsp;</span></span><script type=\"text/javascript\"> jQuery('#footnote_plugin_tooltip__1_15').tooltip({ tip: '#footnote_plugin_tooltip_text__1_15', tipClass: 'footnote_tooltip', effect: 'fade', predelay: 0, fadeInSpeed: 200, delay: 400, fadeOutSpeed: 200, position: 'center right', relative: true, offset: [0, 0], });</script> as did Ḥannah.<span class=\"footnote_referrer\"><a role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\" onclick=\"footnote_moveToReference__1('footnote_plugin_reference__1_16');\" onkeypress=\"footnote_moveToReference__1('footnote_plugin_reference__1_16');\" ><sup id=\"footnote_plugin_tooltip__1_16\" class=\"footnote_plugin_tooltip_text\">[16]</sup></a><span id=\"footnote_plugin_tooltip_text__1_16\" class=\"footnote_tooltip\"> From whose prayer the Gemara learned the halakhah mentioned above on praying alone (ibid Berakhot).&nbsp;</span></span><script type=\"text/javascript\"> jQuery('#footnote_plugin_tooltip__1_16').tooltip({ tip: '#footnote_plugin_tooltip_text__1_16', tipClass: 'footnote_tooltip', effect: 'fade', predelay: 0, fadeInSpeed: 200, delay: 400, fadeOutSpeed: 200, position: 'center right', relative: true, offset: [0, 0], });</script>\n</div>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"vertical-align:top;\">\n<div class=\"liturgy\" lang=\"heb-Hebr\" style=\"text-align: right;\">\n<span class=\"instruction\">{לחש}</span><br />\nלֹא בְקוֹל־גָּדוֹל וּצְעָקָה<br />\nאֶזְעַק הַטֵּה אָזְנְךָ נָּא<br />\nכִּי אֶת נֶֽפֶשׁ נֶאֱנָקָה<br />\nתִּשְׁמַע כְּרַֽחַשׁ־לֶב־חַנָּה\n</div>\n</td>\n<td style=\"vertical-align:top;\">\n<div class=\"french\" lang=\"fra-Latn\" style=\"text-align: left;\">\n&nbsp;<br />\nPuisse mon cri chuchoté<br />\nTe faire tendre l’oreille<br />\nAux paroles d’une âme tourmentée,<br />\nEt t’atteindre comme le vœu qu’a murmuré Hanna.\n</div>\n</td>\n<td style=\"vertical-align:top;\">\n<div class=\"english\" lang=\"eng-Latn\" style=\"text-align: left;\">\n&nbsp;<br />\nNot with shouts and loud cries<span class=\"footnote_referrer\"><a role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\" onclick=\"footnote_moveToReference__1('footnote_plugin_reference__1_17');\" onkeypress=\"footnote_moveToReference__1('footnote_plugin_reference__1_17');\" ><sup id=\"footnote_plugin_tooltip__1_17\" class=\"footnote_plugin_tooltip_text\">[17]</sup></a><span id=\"footnote_plugin_tooltip_text__1_17\" class=\"footnote_tooltip\"> A reference to the biblical story of the confrontation between Eliyahu and the prophets of Baal in 1 Kings 18:26-29. Those who were not answered were those who called to their god with a loud voice.&nbsp;</span></span><script type=\"text/javascript\"> jQuery('#footnote_plugin_tooltip__1_17').tooltip({ tip: '#footnote_plugin_tooltip_text__1_17', tipClass: 'footnote_tooltip', effect: 'fade', predelay: 0, fadeInSpeed: 200, delay: 400, fadeOutSpeed: 200, position: 'center right', relative: true, offset: [0, 0], });</script><br />\nShall I beg You to incline your ear,<span class=\"footnote_referrer\"><a role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\" onclick=\"footnote_moveToReference__1('footnote_plugin_reference__1_18');\" onkeypress=\"footnote_moveToReference__1('footnote_plugin_reference__1_18');\" ><sup id=\"footnote_plugin_tooltip__1_18\" class=\"footnote_plugin_tooltip_text\">[18]</sup></a><span id=\"footnote_plugin_tooltip_text__1_18\" class=\"footnote_tooltip\"> The style of Daniel&#8217;s prayer in Daniel 9:18&nbsp;</span></span><script type=\"text/javascript\"> jQuery('#footnote_plugin_tooltip__1_18').tooltip({ tip: '#footnote_plugin_tooltip_text__1_18', tipClass: 'footnote_tooltip', effect: 'fade', predelay: 0, fadeInSpeed: 200, delay: 400, fadeOutSpeed: 200, position: 'center right', relative: true, offset: [0, 0], });</script><br />\nRather, it is a tormented soul You hear,<br />\nLike the whispering heart of Ḥannah.<span class=\"footnote_referrer\"><a role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\" onclick=\"footnote_moveToReference__1('footnote_plugin_reference__1_19');\" onkeypress=\"footnote_moveToReference__1('footnote_plugin_reference__1_19');\" ><sup id=\"footnote_plugin_tooltip__1_19\" class=\"footnote_plugin_tooltip_text\">[19]</sup></a><span id=\"footnote_plugin_tooltip_text__1_19\" class=\"footnote_tooltip\"> An allusion to the halakhah that one should not pray aloud, which is learned in Berachot 31a from the description of Ḥannah&#8217;s prayer in 1 Samuel 1:13.&nbsp;</span></span><script type=\"text/javascript\"> jQuery('#footnote_plugin_tooltip__1_19').tooltip({ tip: '#footnote_plugin_tooltip_text__1_19', tipClass: 'footnote_tooltip', effect: 'fade', predelay: 0, fadeInSpeed: 200, delay: 400, fadeOutSpeed: 200, position: 'center right', relative: true, offset: [0, 0], });</script>\n</div>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"vertical-align:top;\">\n<div class=\"liturgy\" lang=\"heb-Hebr\" style=\"text-align: right;\">\n<span class=\"instruction\">{חיתוך הדיבור}</span><br />\nנִדְבוֹת פִּי שָׂפָה בְרוּרָה<br />\nאֵלֶֽיךָ קָרֵב קְחָה נָּא<br />\nכְּקוֹל לְוִיִּים בְּשִׁירָה<br />\nוּכְנִֽיעַ שִׂפְתוֹתֵי חַנָּה\n</div>\n</td>\n<td style=\"vertical-align:top;\">\n<div class=\"french\" lang=\"fra-Latn\" style=\"text-align: left;\">\n&nbsp;<br />\nEmbrasse et accepte<br />\nL’offrande qu’articule ma langue,<br />\nComme un chant des Lévites<br />\nEt le bruissement des lèvres de Hanna.\n</div>\n</td>\n<td style=\"vertical-align:top;\">\n<div class=\"english\" lang=\"eng-Latn\" style=\"text-align: left;\">\n&nbsp;<br />\nEmbrace and accept my offering,<br />\nThe clear words of my tongue,<span class=\"footnote_referrer\"><a role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\" onclick=\"footnote_moveToReference__1('footnote_plugin_reference__1_20');\" onkeypress=\"footnote_moveToReference__1('footnote_plugin_reference__1_20');\" ><sup id=\"footnote_plugin_tooltip__1_20\" class=\"footnote_plugin_tooltip_text\">[20]</sup></a><span id=\"footnote_plugin_tooltip_text__1_20\" class=\"footnote_tooltip\"> An allusion to the halakhah that the words of prayer must be pronounced correctly (“cut with the lips”), which is learned in Berachot 26b from the description of the verses about Hannah&#8217;s prayer.&nbsp;</span></span><script type=\"text/javascript\"> jQuery('#footnote_plugin_tooltip__1_20').tooltip({ tip: '#footnote_plugin_tooltip_text__1_20', tipClass: 'footnote_tooltip', effect: 'fade', predelay: 0, fadeInSpeed: 200, delay: 400, fadeOutSpeed: 200, position: 'center right', relative: true, offset: [0, 0], });</script><br />\nLike the voice of the Levites’ song<span class=\"footnote_referrer\"><a role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\" onclick=\"footnote_moveToReference__1('footnote_plugin_reference__1_21');\" onkeypress=\"footnote_moveToReference__1('footnote_plugin_reference__1_21');\" ><sup id=\"footnote_plugin_tooltip__1_21\" class=\"footnote_plugin_tooltip_text\">[21]</sup></a><span id=\"footnote_plugin_tooltip_text__1_21\" class=\"footnote_tooltip\"> A reference to the context in which Ḥannah prayed at the Mishkan. The sacrificial service is the model according to which the three daily prayers were designed, according to Rabbi Joshua ben Levi (Berakhot 26b), as it is said: “And we will pay with our lips” (Hosea 14:3), finds only a hinted expression here, in words borrowed from the verse “Accept, O Lord, the offerings of my lips” (Psalms 119:108). Instead, the prayer is attributed here to the singing of the Levites.&nbsp;</span></span><script type=\"text/javascript\"> jQuery('#footnote_plugin_tooltip__1_21').tooltip({ tip: '#footnote_plugin_tooltip_text__1_21', tipClass: 'footnote_tooltip', effect: 'fade', predelay: 0, fadeInSpeed: 200, delay: 400, fadeOutSpeed: 200, position: 'center right', relative: true, offset: [0, 0], });</script><br />\nAnd the rustle of the lips of Ḥannah.<span class=\"footnote_referrer\"><a role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\" onclick=\"footnote_moveToReference__1('footnote_plugin_reference__1_22');\" onkeypress=\"footnote_moveToReference__1('footnote_plugin_reference__1_22');\" ><sup id=\"footnote_plugin_tooltip__1_22\" class=\"footnote_plugin_tooltip_text\">[22]</sup></a><span id=\"footnote_plugin_tooltip_text__1_22\" class=\"footnote_tooltip\"> according to the description of the verse that is the source of this halakha: “Only her lips were moving” (I Samuel 1:13).&nbsp;</span></span><script type=\"text/javascript\"> jQuery('#footnote_plugin_tooltip__1_22').tooltip({ tip: '#footnote_plugin_tooltip_text__1_22', tipClass: 'footnote_tooltip', effect: 'fade', predelay: 0, fadeInSpeed: 200, delay: 400, fadeOutSpeed: 200, position: 'center right', relative: true, offset: [0, 0], });</script>\n</div>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"vertical-align:top;\">\n<div class=\"liturgy\" lang=\"heb-Hebr\" style=\"text-align: right;\">\n<span class=\"instruction\">{כוונה}</span><br />\nפְּרוֹשׂ עָלֵֽינוּ מְהֵרָה<br />\nסֻכַּת שְׁלוֹמִים מוּכָנָה<br />\nאֲקַוֶּה וַֽאֲדַבְּרָה<br />\nכְּדַבֵּר עַל לִבָּהּ חַנָּה\n</div>\n</td>\n<td style=\"vertical-align:top;\">\n<div class=\"french\" lang=\"fra-Latn\" style=\"text-align: left;\">\n&nbsp;<br />\n«Déploies sur nous promptement<br />\nUn dais de paix!»<br />\nTel est le souhait que j’exprime,<br />\nComme priait jadis Hanna.\n</div>\n</td>\n<td style=\"vertical-align:top;\">\n<div class=\"english\" lang=\"eng-Latn\" style=\"text-align: left;\">\n&nbsp;<br />\n&#8220;Swiftly unfold over us<br />\nA canopy of peace!&#8221;<span class=\"footnote_referrer\"><a role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\" onclick=\"footnote_moveToReference__1('footnote_plugin_reference__1_23');\" onkeypress=\"footnote_moveToReference__1('footnote_plugin_reference__1_23');\" ><sup id=\"footnote_plugin_tooltip__1_23\" class=\"footnote_plugin_tooltip_text\">[23]</sup></a><span id=\"footnote_plugin_tooltip_text__1_23\" class=\"footnote_tooltip\"> From the prayer, &#8220;Hashkivenu&#8221;. This piyyut ends, like many other piyyutim, with hope and prayer.&nbsp;</span></span><script type=\"text/javascript\"> jQuery('#footnote_plugin_tooltip__1_23').tooltip({ tip: '#footnote_plugin_tooltip_text__1_23', tipClass: 'footnote_tooltip', effect: 'fade', predelay: 0, fadeInSpeed: 200, delay: 400, fadeOutSpeed: 200, position: 'center right', relative: true, offset: [0, 0], });</script><br />\nThat is the wish that I admit,<br />\nLike the heartful prayer of Ḥannah.<span class=\"footnote_referrer\"><a role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\" onclick=\"footnote_moveToReference__1('footnote_plugin_reference__1_24');\" onkeypress=\"footnote_moveToReference__1('footnote_plugin_reference__1_24');\" ><sup id=\"footnote_plugin_tooltip__1_24\" class=\"footnote_plugin_tooltip_text\">[24]</sup></a><span id=\"footnote_plugin_tooltip_text__1_24\" class=\"footnote_tooltip\"> I will wait and speak with intention, as Ḥannah spoke from her heart, as described in the verse “And Ḥannah speaks from her heart” (I Samuel 1:13), from which the Gemara learns that one must pray with intention (Berakhot 26b).&nbsp;</span></span><script type=\"text/javascript\"> jQuery('#footnote_plugin_tooltip__1_24').tooltip({ tip: '#footnote_plugin_tooltip_text__1_24', tipClass: 'footnote_tooltip', effect: 'fade', predelay: 0, fadeInSpeed: 200, delay: 400, fadeOutSpeed: 200, position: 'center right', relative: true, offset: [0, 0], });</script>\n</div>\n</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<hr />\n<p>“El asher hasdo” (Hannah’s Prayer) was first published in 2023, as the first of a series of four piyyutim published through the Diwan Ashira Project by Ephraim Kahn. Each piyyut is focused around a different biblical heroine, and sung in relation to a Jewish festival: 1) Hannah’s Prayer (El asher hasdo) for Rosh Hashanah, 2) Song of Miriam, Song of Deborah (Uri Uri) for Shabbat Shirah, 3) Queen Esther’s Prayer (‘Et sha’are armon) for Purim, 4) Ruth and Naomi (Biti ‘arvot) for Shavuot.</p>\n<p>The French translations were contributed by Diwan Ashira. The English translation by Rabbi Josh Weiner. The annotation in English were translated by Aharon Varady from the Hebrew <a href=\"http://<a href=\"https://www.nli.org.il/he/piyut/Piyut1song_013180000000005171/NLI\">&#8220;>here</a>. &#8211;Aharon Varady</p>\n<h3>Recordings</h3>\n<p>Sung by Shir Ifrah<br />\n<iframe loading=\"lazy\" title=\"Shir Ifrah - Hannah&#039;s prayer / El Asher &#039;Hasdo by DIWAN ASHIRA\" width=\"640\" height=\"400\" scrolling=\"no\" frameborder=\"no\" src=\"https://w.soundcloud.com/player/?visual=true&#038;url=https%3A%2F%2Fapi.soundcloud.com%2Ftracks%2F2137539474&#038;show_artwork=true&#038;maxheight=960&#038;maxwidth=640\"></iframe></p>\n<p>Sung by Ariel Danan<br />\n<a href=\"https://drive.google.com/file/d/1n2X5x12ZBdyW464e5vSE_Junj_CYoVnD/view?usp=drivesdk\">https://drive.google.com/file/d/1n2X5x12ZBdyW464e5vSE_Junj_CYoVnD/view?usp=drivesdk</a></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<div class=\"speaker-mute footnotes_reference_container\"> <div class=\"footnote_container_prepare\"><p><span role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\" class=\"footnote_reference_container_label pointer\" onclick=\"footnote_expand_collapse_reference_container__1();\">Notes</span><span role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\" class=\"footnote_reference_container_collapse_button\" style=\"display: none;; display: none;\" onclick=\"footnote_expand_collapse_reference_container__1();\"></span></p></div> <div id=\"footnote_references_container__1\" style=\"\"><table class=\"footnotes_table footnote-reference-container\"><caption class=\"accessibility\">Notes</caption> <tbody> \r\n\r\n<tr class=\"footnotes_plugin_reference_row\"> <th scope=\"row\" id=\"footnote_plugin_reference__1_1\" class=\"footnote_plugin_index pointer\" onclick=\"footnote_moveToAnchor__1('footnote_plugin_tooltip__1_1');\"><a role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\" class=\"footnote_plugin_link\" >1</a></th> <td class=\"footnote_plugin_text\">Find Genesis 27:27</td></tr>\r\n\r\n<tr class=\"footnotes_plugin_reference_row\"> <th scope=\"row\" id=\"footnote_plugin_reference__1_2\" class=\"footnote_plugin_index pointer\" onclick=\"footnote_moveToAnchor__1('footnote_plugin_tooltip__1_2');\"><a role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\" class=\"footnote_plugin_link\" >2</a></th> <td class=\"footnote_plugin_text\">Find Exodus 25:8, Exodus 29:45</td></tr>\r\n\r\n<tr class=\"footnotes_plugin_reference_row\"> <th scope=\"row\" id=\"footnote_plugin_reference__1_3\" class=\"footnote_plugin_index pointer\" onclick=\"footnote_moveToAnchor__1('footnote_plugin_tooltip__1_3');\"><a role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\" class=\"footnote_plugin_link\" >3</a></th> <td class=\"footnote_plugin_text\">The presence of an <em>edah</em> (congregation) is required for the recitation of “sacred words.” Find Berachot 21b, Megillah 23b</td></tr>\r\n\r\n<tr class=\"footnotes_plugin_reference_row\"> <th scope=\"row\" id=\"footnote_plugin_reference__1_4\" class=\"footnote_plugin_index pointer\" onclick=\"footnote_moveToAnchor__1('footnote_plugin_tooltip__1_4');\"><a role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\" class=\"footnote_plugin_link\" >4</a></th> <td class=\"footnote_plugin_text\">Per Jeremiah 14:10, a people accustomed to traveling.</td></tr>\r\n\r\n<tr class=\"footnotes_plugin_reference_row\"> <th scope=\"row\" id=\"footnote_plugin_reference__1_5\" class=\"footnote_plugin_index pointer\" onclick=\"footnote_moveToAnchor__1('footnote_plugin_tooltip__1_5');\"><a role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\" class=\"footnote_plugin_link\" >5</a></th> <td class=\"footnote_plugin_text\">An allusion to the statement of Rav Hamnuna in Berakhot 31a: “How many great halakhot can be learned from the verses of Ḥannah&#8217;s prayer!”</td></tr>\r\n\r\n<tr class=\"footnotes_plugin_reference_row\"> <th scope=\"row\" id=\"footnote_plugin_reference__1_6\" class=\"footnote_plugin_index pointer\" onclick=\"footnote_moveToAnchor__1('footnote_plugin_tooltip__1_6');\"><a role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\" class=\"footnote_plugin_link\" >6</a></th> <td class=\"footnote_plugin_text\">According to Ḥannah&#8217;s self-description in I Samuel 1:10</td></tr>\r\n\r\n<tr class=\"footnotes_plugin_reference_row\"> <th scope=\"row\" id=\"footnote_plugin_reference__1_7\" class=\"footnote_plugin_index pointer\" onclick=\"footnote_moveToAnchor__1('footnote_plugin_tooltip__1_7');\"><a role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\" class=\"footnote_plugin_link\" >7</a></th> <td class=\"footnote_plugin_text\">Prayer is called “work that is in the heart” in Tractate Ta&#8217;anit 2:1</td></tr>\r\n\r\n<tr class=\"footnotes_plugin_reference_row\"> <th scope=\"row\" id=\"footnote_plugin_reference__1_8\" class=\"footnote_plugin_index pointer\" onclick=\"footnote_moveToAnchor__1('footnote_plugin_tooltip__1_8');\"><a role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\" class=\"footnote_plugin_link\" >8</a></th> <td class=\"footnote_plugin_text\">So that she may succeed in praying to You with joy, as stated in the Baraita: One does not stand to pray [&#8230;] except with the joy of a mitsvah (Berakhot 31a).</td></tr>\r\n\r\n<tr class=\"footnotes_plugin_reference_row\"> <th scope=\"row\" id=\"footnote_plugin_reference__1_9\" class=\"footnote_plugin_index pointer\" onclick=\"footnote_moveToAnchor__1('footnote_plugin_tooltip__1_9');\"><a role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\" class=\"footnote_plugin_link\" >9</a></th> <td class=\"footnote_plugin_text\">An allusion to the halakhah that a drunk person is forbidden to pray, which is learned (in Berakhot there) from Eli&#8217;s description of Ḥannah&#8217;s prayer in I Samuel. This expression is taken from the verse “and drunk, but not with wine” (Isaiah 51:21) and means to lose one&#8217;s mind as a result of distress.</td></tr>\r\n\r\n<tr class=\"footnotes_plugin_reference_row\"> <th scope=\"row\" id=\"footnote_plugin_reference__1_10\" class=\"footnote_plugin_index pointer\" onclick=\"footnote_moveToAnchor__1('footnote_plugin_tooltip__1_10');\"><a role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\" class=\"footnote_plugin_link\" >10</a></th> <td class=\"footnote_plugin_text\">Ibid I Samuel 1:10</td></tr>\r\n\r\n<tr class=\"footnotes_plugin_reference_row\"> <th scope=\"row\" id=\"footnote_plugin_reference__1_11\" class=\"footnote_plugin_index pointer\" onclick=\"footnote_moveToAnchor__1('footnote_plugin_tooltip__1_11');\"><a role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\" class=\"footnote_plugin_link\" >11</a></th> <td class=\"footnote_plugin_text\">Alone by myself, an allusion to the words of the Gemara that it is forbidden to sit within four cubits of a person who is praying (Berakhot 31b).</td></tr>\r\n\r\n<tr class=\"footnotes_plugin_reference_row\"> <th scope=\"row\" id=\"footnote_plugin_reference__1_12\" class=\"footnote_plugin_index pointer\" onclick=\"footnote_moveToAnchor__1('footnote_plugin_tooltip__1_12');\"><a role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\" class=\"footnote_plugin_link\" >12</a></th> <td class=\"footnote_plugin_text\">to pray, as Ḥannah said in relation to her prayer: “I am the woman who stands here before you praying” (I Samuel 1:26).</td></tr>\r\n\r\n<tr class=\"footnotes_plugin_reference_row\"> <th scope=\"row\" id=\"footnote_plugin_reference__1_13\" class=\"footnote_plugin_index pointer\" onclick=\"footnote_moveToAnchor__1('footnote_plugin_tooltip__1_13');\"><a role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\" class=\"footnote_plugin_link\" >13</a></th> <td class=\"footnote_plugin_text\">According to Psalms 118:25</td></tr>\r\n\r\n<tr class=\"footnotes_plugin_reference_row\"> <th scope=\"row\" id=\"footnote_plugin_reference__1_14\" class=\"footnote_plugin_index pointer\" onclick=\"footnote_moveToAnchor__1('footnote_plugin_tooltip__1_14');\"><a role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\" class=\"footnote_plugin_link\" >14</a></th> <td class=\"footnote_plugin_text\">According to Psalms 42:3</td></tr>\r\n\r\n<tr class=\"footnotes_plugin_reference_row\"> <th scope=\"row\" id=\"footnote_plugin_reference__1_15\" class=\"footnote_plugin_index pointer\" onclick=\"footnote_moveToAnchor__1('footnote_plugin_tooltip__1_15');\"><a role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\" class=\"footnote_plugin_link\" >15</a></th> <td class=\"footnote_plugin_text\">In the style of <em>baqashah</em> and <em>tefilah</em> (in plea and prayer)</td></tr>\r\n\r\n<tr class=\"footnotes_plugin_reference_row\"> <th scope=\"row\" id=\"footnote_plugin_reference__1_16\" class=\"footnote_plugin_index pointer\" onclick=\"footnote_moveToAnchor__1('footnote_plugin_tooltip__1_16');\"><a role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\" class=\"footnote_plugin_link\" >16</a></th> <td class=\"footnote_plugin_text\">From whose prayer the Gemara learned the halakhah mentioned above on praying alone (ibid Berakhot).</td></tr>\r\n\r\n<tr class=\"footnotes_plugin_reference_row\"> <th scope=\"row\" id=\"footnote_plugin_reference__1_17\" class=\"footnote_plugin_index pointer\" onclick=\"footnote_moveToAnchor__1('footnote_plugin_tooltip__1_17');\"><a role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\" class=\"footnote_plugin_link\" >17</a></th> <td class=\"footnote_plugin_text\">A reference to the biblical story of the confrontation between Eliyahu and the prophets of Baal in 1 Kings 18:26-29. Those who were not answered were those who called to their god with a loud voice.</td></tr>\r\n\r\n<tr class=\"footnotes_plugin_reference_row\"> <th scope=\"row\" id=\"footnote_plugin_reference__1_18\" class=\"footnote_plugin_index pointer\" onclick=\"footnote_moveToAnchor__1('footnote_plugin_tooltip__1_18');\"><a role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\" class=\"footnote_plugin_link\" >18</a></th> <td class=\"footnote_plugin_text\">The style of Daniel&#8217;s prayer in Daniel 9:18</td></tr>\r\n\r\n<tr class=\"footnotes_plugin_reference_row\"> <th scope=\"row\" id=\"footnote_plugin_reference__1_19\" class=\"footnote_plugin_index pointer\" onclick=\"footnote_moveToAnchor__1('footnote_plugin_tooltip__1_19');\"><a role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\" class=\"footnote_plugin_link\" >19</a></th> <td class=\"footnote_plugin_text\">An allusion to the halakhah that one should not pray aloud, which is learned in Berachot 31a from the description of Ḥannah&#8217;s prayer in 1 Samuel 1:13.</td></tr>\r\n\r\n<tr class=\"footnotes_plugin_reference_row\"> <th scope=\"row\" id=\"footnote_plugin_reference__1_20\" class=\"footnote_plugin_index pointer\" onclick=\"footnote_moveToAnchor__1('footnote_plugin_tooltip__1_20');\"><a role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\" class=\"footnote_plugin_link\" >20</a></th> <td class=\"footnote_plugin_text\">An allusion to the halakhah that the words of prayer must be pronounced correctly (“cut with the lips”), which is learned in Berachot 26b from the description of the verses about Hannah&#8217;s prayer.</td></tr>\r\n\r\n<tr class=\"footnotes_plugin_reference_row\"> <th scope=\"row\" id=\"footnote_plugin_reference__1_21\" class=\"footnote_plugin_index pointer\" onclick=\"footnote_moveToAnchor__1('footnote_plugin_tooltip__1_21');\"><a role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\" class=\"footnote_plugin_link\" >21</a></th> <td class=\"footnote_plugin_text\">A reference to the context in which Ḥannah prayed at the Mishkan. The sacrificial service is the model according to which the three daily prayers were designed, according to Rabbi Joshua ben Levi (Berakhot 26b), as it is said: “And we will pay with our lips” (Hosea 14:3), finds only a hinted expression here, in words borrowed from the verse “Accept, O Lord, the offerings of my lips” (Psalms 119:108). Instead, the prayer is attributed here to the singing of the Levites.</td></tr>\r\n\r\n<tr class=\"footnotes_plugin_reference_row\"> <th scope=\"row\" id=\"footnote_plugin_reference__1_22\" class=\"footnote_plugin_index pointer\" onclick=\"footnote_moveToAnchor__1('footnote_plugin_tooltip__1_22');\"><a role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\" class=\"footnote_plugin_link\" >22</a></th> <td class=\"footnote_plugin_text\">according to the description of the verse that is the source of this halakha: “Only her lips were moving” (I Samuel 1:13).</td></tr>\r\n\r\n<tr class=\"footnotes_plugin_reference_row\"> <th scope=\"row\" id=\"footnote_plugin_reference__1_23\" class=\"footnote_plugin_index pointer\" onclick=\"footnote_moveToAnchor__1('footnote_plugin_tooltip__1_23');\"><a role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\" class=\"footnote_plugin_link\" >23</a></th> <td class=\"footnote_plugin_text\">From the prayer, &#8220;Hashkivenu&#8221;. This piyyut ends, like many other piyyutim, with hope and prayer.</td></tr>\r\n\r\n<tr class=\"footnotes_plugin_reference_row\"> <th scope=\"row\" id=\"footnote_plugin_reference__1_24\" class=\"footnote_plugin_index pointer\" onclick=\"footnote_moveToAnchor__1('footnote_plugin_tooltip__1_24');\"><a role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\" class=\"footnote_plugin_link\" >24</a></th> <td class=\"footnote_plugin_text\">I will wait and speak with intention, as Ḥannah spoke from her heart, as described in the verse “And Ḥannah speaks from her heart” (I Samuel 1:13), from which the Gemara learns that one must pray with intention (Berakhot 26b).</td></tr>\r\n\r\n </tbody> </table> </div></div><script type=\"text/javascript\"> function footnote_expand_reference_container__1() { jQuery('#footnote_references_container__1').show(); jQuery('#footnote_reference_container_collapse_button__1').text('−'); } function footnote_collapse_reference_container__1() { jQuery('#footnote_references_container__1').hide(); jQuery('#footnote_reference_container_collapse_button__1').text('+'); } function footnote_expand_collapse_reference_container__1() { if (jQuery('#footnote_references_container__1').is(':hidden')) { footnote_expand_reference_container__1(); } else { footnote_collapse_reference_container__1(); } } function footnote_moveToReference__1(p_str_TargetID) { footnote_expand_reference_container__1(); var l_obj_Target = jQuery('#' + p_str_TargetID); if (l_obj_Target.length) { jQuery( 'html, body' ).delay( 0 ); jQuery('html, body').animate({ scrollTop: l_obj_Target.offset().top - window.innerHeight * 0.2 }, 380); } } function footnote_moveToAnchor__1(p_str_TargetID) { footnote_expand_reference_container__1(); var l_obj_Target = jQuery('#' + p_str_TargetID); if (l_obj_Target.length) { jQuery( 'html, body' ).delay( 0 ); jQuery('html, body').animate({ scrollTop: l_obj_Target.offset().top - window.innerHeight * 0.2 }, 380); } }</script>",
